This cephalopod inspired robot is a ghoulish spektor that haunts archeotech ruins.

It is a remix of Akewea's Sci-Fi Sphere Drone (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5266420) and Franklima260's Mini Servo Arm (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/sci-fi-sphere-drone)

The arms are fully posable with ball & socket joints at the shoulder, elbow, and wrist.

Since the attachment point to the base is pretty small, I've included 4 additional versions of the tentacles with a rod cutout for pinning of the following sizes
- 1mm brass rod (1.1mm hole)
- 1.5mm brass rod (1.6mm hole)
- 0.8mm thin paperclip (0.9mm hole)
- 1.15mm thick paperclip (1.25mm hole)

I removed the hatch ring from the gunner and changed the attachments for the shield and the stubbers to fit the plastic bits. It's quick and dirty, but the messy parts are facing to the hull and shouldn't be an issue.

Original gunner by FelixTheCrazy adapted by KarnageKing.

Edit2: Added some other parts that are useful when building the plastic kit. Magnet holding counterparts for the turret and stubber gunner hatch, spacers for the front bumper.

These remixed robos have been broken up for posing! Only the one weapon option - I struggled to get them this far. (full credit to original creator Orange Blue Hue's Tabletop Simulator files)

You have separate pieces for the head, torso and legs. 3D builder is a lovely lil tool so I've added a compatible format for that so you can quickly reposition the parts in there, then save-as stl.

What's changed? RIVETS. SO. MANY. RIVETS. Also I removed the crude skull chest logo, one is blank for customising, the other has a mechanics logo embossed, enjoy!

Four included poses and a builder to do your own. Happy printing!

Something I've made on couple of weeks ago on few free evenings. I wanted to upload it when I've test printed it but could not find a moment to do it so here it is.

It always bothered me that mechanicum leaves so much flesh on their tools of war when head is just enough. It is my version of Kataphron Destroyer with it's standard weapons. It should be roughly the same size as the original.

Most parts should print fairy well with default orientation and supports. Weapons might need to be sliced in half.
